---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Lore — itsthelore">
  <p class="eyebrow">Lore</p>
  <h1>Requirements-as-code for AI-assisted product teams.</h1>
  <p class="prose">
    Lore models product-management knowledge — requirements, decisions,
    roadmaps, prompts, and designs — as deterministic, typed Markdown
    artifacts. Its engine, <strong>RAC</strong>, validates that knowledge as
    a corpus, so agents and humans work from the same grounded source of
    truth instead of drifting docs and stale memory.
  </p>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <a class="card" href="/rac-core/">
      <h3>rac-core</h3>
      <p>The RAC engine and CLI — artifact schemas, validation, relationships, and the corpus toolchain.</p>
    </a>
    <div class="card disabled">
      <h3>rac-ci</h3>
      <p>CI delivery — Watchkeeper, Gatekeeper, and audit actions. Coming soon.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card disabled">
      <h3>rac-connectors</h3>
      <p>Inbound and outbound integrations. Coming soon.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
